{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"faint-ethnic-merganser","description":"# Stage-2 bounded LLM pairwise overlap judge (advisory findings + suggested link commands)\n\n## Why\nPrecision lives in stage 2, not in any similarity threshold. A bounded LLM pairwise judge over the ~20 stage-1 candidates is where \"duplicate vs depends-on vs related-but-distinct vs unrelated\" is decided — with the FP controls the research converged on.\n\n## What\n- A pairwise judge (`RunRequest`, structured output) over each stage-1 candidate: both orderings aggregated (position bias), REQUIRED to cite the shared concrete artifact (same root cause / same file / same user-visible behavior), DEFAULTS to \"related-but-distinct\" without one, and abstains on low confidence. Cost is bounded by K (flat in corpus size).\n- Emit at most ~3 highest-confidence candidates as ADVISORY findings. Each finding names the counterpart ticket, the relation (duplicates/supersedes/depends_on), the cited shared artifact, and a ready-to-run `rebar link <A> <B> <rel>` command. Never auto-links.\n- Optional cascade: cheap pre-filter → strong judge only on survivors, to bound cost further.\n\n## Scope\n- IN scope: the judge op + rubric prompt + output schema, ordering-aggregation, abstain, the ~3-cap, the suggested-command formatting, eval cases for precision (related-but-distinct must NOT be flagged) and recall (true duplicate IS flagged). OUT: retrieval (S5), wiring (S7).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Judges each candidate pair in both orderings and aggregates (order-flip does not change the verdict for clear cases).\n- [ ] A finding is emitted only when the judge cites a concrete shared artifact; absent one, the pair is classified related-but-distinct and NOT surfaced.\n- [ ] At most ~3 candidates surface, each as an advisory finding with the counterpart id, relation, cited artifact, and a copy-paste `rebar link …` command.\n- [ ] Never mutates links.\n- [ ] Eval spec: a \"related-but-distinct\" pair is NOT flagged (precision) and a genuine duplicate IS flagged (recall); K and any confidence threshold are tuned on the labeled fixture.","id":"9022-d3e3-e97f-47e3","parent_id":"bd83-c56f-1f72-4ef2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Stage-2 bounded LLM pairwise overlap judge (advisory findings + suggested link commands)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783568207187823001,"uuid":"18a8d486-b3db-4f17-b211-3d33cef4dfad"}